name: A Visual Delight
description:
This photograph is taken from the Queen's room inside a Palace which was establishment of the Udaipur city by the King "Maharana Udai Singh II" and his successor Maharanas over a period of the next 400 years. Where royals used to live and continue living for more than 400 years. It was built over a period of nearly 400 years, with contributions from several rulers of the Mewar dynasty.

It was later called "The City Palace"

The swing was found in Queens room, and stays there since 1559. The art is a glimpse of how astonishing and beautiful  place it is.
